Entry.87:
)
Things nice & quiet,doing sapping & outpost duty alternatively. Two of our fellows were shot yesterday only a few yards

from our "tent"by a sniper, one died immediately, but the other was only slightly wounded. Two others were wounded, one a stretcher bearer very seriously, & the other was hit through the ribs when on outpost duty. It was telephoned in to us last night from hill 60, on our left & about two miles distant that the Turks were using poisonous gases there, we got our respirators in case of emergency but fortunately did not require their use. Held our first Church service today on the "battlefield".

Entry.105:
)
Still preparing Winter Quarters.
Yesterday the warships opened a very heavy bombardment of a Turkish Railway bridge some miles inland & succeeded in demolishing it. The Guard which for the past couple of weeks has been at Imbrosreturned today.
